oc:kn_30cf6fbd a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring command documentation sections" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Show examples before explanations: demonstrate usage with concrete examples, then provide detailed explanations." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Users learn faster from examples than from abstract descriptions, and examples provide copy-paste-ready starting points." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_5271dd95 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing the frontmatter description field" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Command description in frontmatter must be under 60 characters and clearly describe what the command does." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Short descriptions are displayed in command lists and autocomplete; they must be scannable and precise." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6ab5f568 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating a complete command template" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use 8 mandatory documentation comment sections: PURPOSE, USAGE, ARGUMENTS, EXAMPLES, REQUIREMENTS, RELATED COMMANDS, TROUBLESHOOTING, CHANGELOG." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Consistent section structure makes commands predictable and ensures no critical documentation is missing." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6e4c254f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When maintaining long-lived commands" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Documentation drifts out of sync with implementation over time. Version your commands and maintain a CHANGELOG section to track what changed when." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Outdated documentation is worse than no documentation because it erodes trust. Changelogs create accountability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_8e38d20b a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When authoring any slash command" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Documentation should be embedded in the command file itself via HTML comments, making it immediately accessible to users and maintainers without requiring external files." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Embedded documentation travels with the command, stays in sync, and is always available where the command is used." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b99c31bb a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing error messages in commands" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never write bare error messages like 'ERROR: something went wrong'. Always include the cause, meaning, and concrete recovery steps." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Unhelpful error messages frustrate users and increase support burden. Actionable errors enable self-service resolution." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_dc922b5b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing multi-step command implementations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use inline HTML comments (<!-- SECTION -->) to document validation, analysis, and output sections within command logic so maintainers understand code structure." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Inline section comments serve as a table of contents for the command logic, aiding maintenance and debugging." .

oc:kn_e23889b9 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When organizing command documentation layout" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use progressive disclosure: place basic usage info first (description, usage syntax, simple examples), then detailed sections (arguments, troubleshooting, changelog) for users who need more." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Most users need quick answers; only power users need deep details. Layering prevents information overload." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_f0d9f0c5 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When preparing a command for release" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before releasing a command, verify: description is clear, argument-hint documents all arguments, usage examples exist, error messages are helpful, requirements are documented, changelog is maintained, and examples actually work." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The documentation checklist catches common omissions that degrade user experience." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

